Questions

1. What is your project idea (as determined by your team and approved by your teacher)?
CS Recruting Website

2. What what kind of web site is it (Community, Existing Industry, Startup)
Community website.

3. What problem does your project solve?
Informing people about the CS classes so they can learn more about them. 

4. Is it a “vitamin” or a “painkiller”? Why?
Vitamin because it is a nice to have but not a necessity.

5. How does your project solve the problem?


6. Is your idea similar to another product? If so, how is your idea better/different (what is your “secret sauce” as described in the video)?
There is a CS recruiting page on the CS4RI website with some information however this site might not be the first "go to" location for students.
There is also the code.org site that has a lot of recruiting information on there. However, it is removed from the local aspect of our students. 
Our idea would be better because it will be flashier, more appealing, and more student centered, offering more incentives for students to visit it. 

7. Describe the likely users of your web site.
Students that don't yet know they are interested in CS
Teachers to recruit potential CS students

